    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nNeovim does not handle the ServerCancelled LSP error code. Ideally, it should be managed in conjunction with [ServerCancellationData](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#diagnosticServerCancellationData). However, an initial solution would be just suppressing the error.\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/70210066/4e27332b-9132-4237-977b-2fcd1a554d25)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n--- minimal_init.lua\r\nlocal pattern = \"luau\"\r\nlocal cmd = { \"luau-lsp\", \"lsp\" }\r\nlocal root_markers = { \".luaurc\" }\r\n\r\nlocal settings = {\r\n  [\"luau-lsp\"] = {\r\n    sourcemap = {\r\n      enabled = false,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\r\n  pattern = pattern,\r\n  callback = function(args)\r\n    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, \":p:h\") or nil\r\n    vim.lsp.start {\r\n      name = \"luau-lsp\",\r\n      cmd = cmd,\r\n      root_dir = root_dir,\r\n      settings = settings,\r\n    }\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n`nvim -u minimal_init.lua test.luau`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nDo not show -32802 (ServerCancelled) error.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2135+g98a4ed0a1\r\n\r\n### Language server name/version\r\n\r\nluau-lsp@1.27.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 10\r\n\r\n### Log file\r\n\r\n_No response_",
